UNIT 3 â€“ Introduction to Threat Modelling
Unit Overview

This unit introduced threat modelling concepts and techniques, including STRIDE, DREAD, attack trees, and hybrid frameworks such as PASTA.

Artefacts

STRIDE vs DREAD comparison table

Threat vs vulnerability notes

Reflection

I learned that threat modelling provides a proactive way to identify security weaknesses before incidents occur. Comparing multiple models showed that no single framework is sufficient in all contexts, reinforcing the importance of selecting or combining techniques based on system complexity and risk tolerance.

References

Shostack, A. et al. (2020). Threat Modeling Manifesto.
https://www.threatmodelingmanifesto.org

